; Cristian - unfortunately Debian does not have PPA's :( Thus the only way to install this in stretch is to compile it yourself.; Debian can use PPAs from Ubuntu. Simply you have to add the repo line to /etc/apt/sources.list.d/nameoftherepo.list and add the public key for the repo. Or install in your Debian the package 'software-properties-common' and add the PPA like in Ubuntu. But, only use PPAs for Xenial 16.04 that is the LTS.; +Tatoconlinux please don't do that - stretch is GTK+3.22 based. Ubuntu 16.04 is GTK+3.18 based. Very different - it really isnt recommended to install compiled packages from one distro into another.
